node.title: SA records two COVID deaths and 1,289 new cases
node.alt: COVID-19 vaccination rollout at Elizabeth in Adelaide's northern suburbs.
node.description: Two women aged in their 80s have died from COVID-19 in South Australia, which today reported 1,289 new cases.
node.content:
["South Australia has recorded another two COVID-linked deaths in the latest reporting period \u2014 both women aged in their 80s.", "The number of new cases is 1,289, which is slightly fewer than yesterday.", "More to come.", "", "
Data shows many older Australians haven't had their booster
"]
